OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,420,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1773911088
OL,3,CMore than 60 firefighters at scene of
OL,4,Cthatch roof fire
OL,6,F"And then from the front and the back
OL,7,Fwe're now looking to extinguish the
OL,8,Ffire where we can because of the risk
OL,9,Fto the environment from the CAFS and
OL,10,Falso the fact that it's very difficult
OL,11,Fto extinguish a thatched fire, if we
OL,12,Fcan't get too close to it or can't get
OL,13,Finto the building.
OL,15,F"It's safer to do what we call a
OL,16,Fcontrolled burn, which is where we let
OL,17,Fthe fire burn through and then, using
OL,18,Fthe aerial ladder platforms, we can
OL,19,Fthen get above the fire and put the
OL,20,Ffire out that way."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
